1
00:00:09,109 --> 00:00:10,542
- Let me put an apron on you.
- Okay.

2
00:00:10,543 --> 00:00:11,578
Here we go.

3
00:00:12,746 --> 00:00:15,882
SENIOR CARE HOME
GREEN FLAT EAST SHINJUKU

4
00:00:20,720 --> 00:00:22,121
Would you like some more?

5
00:00:22,122 --> 00:00:23,857
Tien.

6
00:00:24,924 --> 00:00:25,925
Tien!

7
00:00:35,168 --> 00:00:36,503
Hayakawa?

8
00:00:37,670 --> 00:00:38,938
Where's Betsushima?

9
00:00:43,276 --> 00:00:44,911
How did this happen?

10
00:00:46,546 --> 00:00:48,014
So, who did that?

11
00:00:48,581 --> 00:00:51,183
It was like that already when I got there.

12
00:00:51,184 --> 00:00:52,851
Come this way, please.

13
00:00:52,852 --> 00:00:54,353
I see.

14
00:00:54,354 --> 00:00:56,156
Can you tell me how long ago it was?

15
00:00:57,257 --> 00:00:58,858
What on earth is going on?

16
00:00:59,359 --> 00:01:03,429
They're saying that Tien had
Mr. Minami's tablet in his locker.

17
00:01:03,430 --> 00:01:05,464
- What? Did he steal it?
- So the tablet

18
00:01:05,465 --> 00:01:06,666
was inside?

19
00:01:07,500 --> 00:01:10,937
I can't believe it at all.
I thought he was such a nice guy.

20
00:01:11,438 --> 00:01:14,606
Could it be that Mr. Matsumura
always hollering at him

21
00:01:14,607 --> 00:01:16,141
pushed him over the edge?

22
00:01:16,142 --> 00:01:18,645
That's enough. It's been found,
so let's move on.

23
00:01:19,345 --> 00:01:22,315
We need you to come down
to the station and talk to us.

24
00:01:28,221 --> 00:01:32,024
HIGASHI SHINJUKU POLICE STATION
INTERNATIONAL INVESTIGATION DIVISION

25
00:01:32,025 --> 00:01:34,494
"I swear, I didn't steal it."

26
00:01:34,994 --> 00:01:36,528
But still,

27
00:01:36,529 --> 00:01:40,400
the tablet was found in your locker,
you know.

28
00:01:49,175 --> 00:01:51,177
"But I'm telling you the truth."

29
00:01:52,278 --> 00:01:53,712
Then tell me this.

30
00:01:53,713 --> 00:01:55,080
Why do you think

31
00:01:55,081 --> 00:01:59,419
a resident's personal belonging
was found in your locker?

32
00:02:25,678 --> 00:02:29,314
Look over here!
You're totally hooked on it, huh?

33
00:02:29,315 --> 00:02:31,717
No, no, no.
I just happened to pass by the shop.

34
00:02:31,718 --> 00:02:35,488
You don't have to be shy about it,
you know.

35
00:02:36,055 --> 00:02:37,090
I'm not being shy...

36
00:02:37,991 --> 00:02:40,226
By the way, are you available on Saturday?

37
00:02:41,361 --> 00:02:42,194
On Saturday?

38
00:02:42,195 --> 00:02:45,030
Momiji's having some people over
at her place.

39
00:02:45,031 --> 00:02:46,833
Would you like to join us?

40
00:02:47,667 --> 00:02:50,136
No, thank you.

41
00:02:50,770 --> 00:02:51,970
I heard

42
00:02:51,971 --> 00:02:55,608
Momiji's making Vietnamese food.

43
00:02:59,312 --> 00:03:01,881
If you're that hooked on <i>banh mi,</i>

44
00:03:02,682 --> 00:03:05,985
I'm sure you'll really enjoy it.

45
00:03:07,086 --> 00:03:10,455
Come on. It's a great opportunity.
Let's go.

46
00:03:10,456 --> 00:03:12,224
Vietnamese food is calling you.

47
00:03:12,225 --> 00:03:13,592
Actually,

48
00:03:13,593 --> 00:03:15,728
I think I have a meeting.

49
00:03:16,296 --> 00:03:17,430
Oh, look. It's Momiji.

50
00:03:18,364 --> 00:03:19,199
Excuse me.

51
00:03:20,066 --> 00:03:23,035
Would you consider holding off
on starting Tien's booking?

52
00:03:23,036 --> 00:03:24,002
What?

53
00:03:24,003 --> 00:03:27,272
I just find it hard to believe
that he actually stole.

54
00:03:27,273 --> 00:03:30,776
At least, please wait until someone
from a support organization arrives.

55
00:03:30,777 --> 00:03:32,045
Would you please consider?

56
00:03:32,545 --> 00:03:33,478
What's the matter?

57
00:03:33,479 --> 00:03:35,815
Stay out of this.
It's none of your business.

58
00:03:37,850 --> 00:03:39,385
Hey, stop. Don't barge in there.

59
00:03:48,394 --> 00:03:49,462
You are...

60
00:03:51,197 --> 00:03:52,265
Excuse me.

61
00:03:54,601 --> 00:03:55,768
How did this happen?

62
00:03:56,402 --> 00:03:58,770
Mr. Tarao, he's seriously injured
and running a fever too.

63
00:03:58,771 --> 00:04:00,005
Are you kidding me?

64
00:04:00,006 --> 00:04:00,907
Arikeeno,

65
00:04:01,674 --> 00:04:02,941
find a hospital.

66
00:04:02,942 --> 00:04:04,276
What? Hospital?

67
00:04:04,277 --> 00:04:05,444
I'll go with him then.

68
00:04:05,445 --> 00:04:07,046
I'm going to bring some ice.

69
00:04:22,629 --> 00:04:25,932
What caused such a serious injury,
like a bone fracture?

70
00:04:30,503 --> 00:04:33,473
And you had those terrible bruises.

71
00:04:34,107 --> 00:04:36,609
Let me wipe the sweat from your body.

72
00:04:37,176 --> 00:04:39,345
I'll be careful
not to touch the painful areas.

73
00:04:42,148 --> 00:04:44,349
Here, just say that it was
in the suspect's locker.

74
00:04:44,350 --> 00:04:45,751
- Turn this in today.
- Okay.

75
00:04:45,752 --> 00:04:47,219
Hey!

76
00:04:47,220 --> 00:04:49,087
Wait. Hold it right there.

77
00:04:49,088 --> 00:04:51,690
You heard what Miss Imai said
on the phone, didn't you?

78
00:04:51,691 --> 00:04:55,060
He has bruises on his abdomen.
He might have been assaulted, so--

79
00:04:55,061 --> 00:04:57,429
It doesn't necessarily mean
he was assaulted.

80
00:04:57,430 --> 00:04:59,732
He might have picked a fight.

81
00:05:00,566 --> 00:05:02,935
Besides, he's a suspect in a theft case.

82
00:05:04,070 --> 00:05:07,707
But still, could it be as simple as him
just stealing the tablet?

83
00:05:08,274 --> 00:05:10,742
Don't you think
we should investigate properly?

84
00:05:10,743 --> 00:05:13,146
If that's what you think, then you do it.

85
00:05:15,315 --> 00:05:16,783
May I?

86
00:05:17,750 --> 00:05:19,719
- Sure.
- Thank you so much.

87
00:05:20,987 --> 00:05:21,854
Up we go.

88
00:05:22,355 --> 00:05:24,190
- I'm heading out there then.
- All right.

89
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:29,562
I'm surprised you didn't get mad at her.

90
00:05:30,129 --> 00:05:31,664
Let's see how far she goes.

91
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:36,435
We're after the same goal anyway.
That's called "teamwork", baby.

92
00:05:36,436 --> 00:05:40,539
If you two just let her have her way,
she'll get out of control.

93
00:05:40,540 --> 00:05:41,873
Don't you know the proverb,

94
00:05:41,874 --> 00:05:45,277
"The heat and the cold
last only up to the equinoxes?"

95
00:05:45,278 --> 00:05:47,346
I have no idea what you're trying to say.

96
00:05:47,347 --> 00:05:48,514
You mean, "Three cold, four warm?"

97
00:05:49,382 --> 00:05:51,616
It's always one after another with you.

98
00:05:51,617 --> 00:05:53,986
I do have to handle things
one after another.

99
00:05:57,256 --> 00:05:59,091
But I think you're all right

100
00:05:59,092 --> 00:06:00,393
with the way you are now.

101
00:06:01,627 --> 00:06:02,628
Huh?

102
00:06:03,363 --> 00:06:04,630
Well, um...

103
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:08,634
Oh, I almost forgot.

104
00:06:09,135 --> 00:06:11,204
Thanks for finding the hospital.

105
00:06:13,740 --> 00:06:15,308
All right then. I'll call you later.

106
00:06:21,848 --> 00:06:24,116
I'm sorry you had to wait.

107
00:06:24,117 --> 00:06:26,752
This is Mr. Abe,
from the support organization that offers

108
00:06:26,753 --> 00:06:28,553
support to Specified Skilled Workers.

109
00:06:28,554 --> 00:06:31,289
I'm Abe from the Meiho Cooperative.

110
00:06:31,290 --> 00:06:32,758
Thank you.

111
00:06:32,759 --> 00:06:34,861
I'm Koda from
the International Investigation Division.

112
00:06:35,862 --> 00:06:39,731
Did you meet with Tien from time to time?

113
00:06:39,732 --> 00:06:40,867
Yes, I did.

114
00:06:41,434 --> 00:06:44,636
Tien came to Japan for the first time
six years ago.

115
00:06:44,637 --> 00:06:46,371
He started out in a rural area.

116
00:06:46,372 --> 00:06:48,373
I heard he worked diligently
for three years

117
00:06:48,374 --> 00:06:50,576
at a senior care home there
as a Specified Skilled Worker.

118
00:06:51,077 --> 00:06:52,845
After that, he went home and got married.

119
00:06:53,413 --> 00:06:57,015
He got the Specified Skilled Worker
Type one visa two years ago

120
00:06:57,016 --> 00:06:58,217
and has been working
at that care home since.

121
00:06:58,951 --> 00:07:00,786
He had some bruises on his body,

122
00:07:00,787 --> 00:07:04,156
which makes me wonder
if he was assaulted at work.

123
00:07:04,157 --> 00:07:08,294
He hasn't come to us for advice
about any trouble at his workplace.

124
00:07:09,695 --> 00:07:13,598
I got the impression that he's been
really enjoying his work lately,

125
00:07:13,599 --> 00:07:16,636
and he even mentioned
that he made a friend at work.

126
00:07:18,271 --> 00:07:19,372
A friend?

127
00:07:20,473 --> 00:07:21,307
Yes.

128
00:07:22,742 --> 00:07:24,376
GREEN FLAT EAST SHINJUKU

129
00:07:24,377 --> 00:07:25,510
<i>In the beginning,</i>

130
00:07:25,511 --> 00:07:29,615
some of our residents
had trust issues with Tien.

131
00:07:30,550 --> 00:07:34,220
Care workers need to touch
people's bodies as part of their work.

132
00:07:34,854 --> 00:07:36,922
Even without racial prejudice,

133
00:07:36,923 --> 00:07:40,326
people can't help but feel awkward
at first.

134
00:07:40,893 --> 00:07:42,394
- Ma'am.
- Yes.

135
00:07:42,395 --> 00:07:43,529
Okay.

136
00:07:45,198 --> 00:07:46,565
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

137
00:07:46,566 --> 00:07:48,700
MR. MUKAI STOOD UP TOO QUICKLY
AND ALMOST FELL

138
00:07:48,701 --> 00:07:51,236
1/11 REFUSED FOOD
LIKES GENTLE PATS ON THE BACK

139
00:07:51,237 --> 00:07:55,541
But in fact, he was an eager learner
and a brilliant guy.

140
00:07:56,309 --> 00:07:58,878
I just never imagined that he would steal.

141
00:08:01,647 --> 00:08:03,014
So, you also think

142
00:08:03,015 --> 00:08:05,318
that he was the one who stole the tablet.

143
00:08:08,087 --> 00:08:08,921
Um, I'm...

144
00:08:10,156 --> 00:08:11,090
To tell you the truth,

145
00:08:11,991 --> 00:08:14,292
he suffered a bone fracture
on the back of his hand.

146
00:08:14,293 --> 00:08:15,560
What?

147
00:08:15,561 --> 00:08:18,598
And it seems there's something
he's keeping from us.

148
00:08:19,398 --> 00:08:22,869
Do you know if there were
any relationship issues in this home?

149
00:08:23,703 --> 00:08:25,103
Well, um...

150
00:08:25,104 --> 00:08:28,406
Some staff members were harsh
in the way they taught him.

151
00:08:28,407 --> 00:08:30,843
But I just don't think anyone
would physically hurt him.

152
00:08:33,179 --> 00:08:34,447
I see.

153
00:08:37,283 --> 00:08:38,350
And...

154
00:08:38,351 --> 00:08:42,220
Do you mind telling me again
what happened yesterday, in detail?

155
00:08:42,221 --> 00:08:43,221
Sure.

156
00:08:43,222 --> 00:08:45,190
‎37TH RYUO TITLE MATCH, GAME 3
‎COMMENTARY! SHOGI LIVE COMMENTARY CH.

157
00:08:45,191 --> 00:08:46,893
<i>It was in the early afternoon.</i>

158
00:08:47,593 --> 00:08:50,029
Matsu-san, it's time for you
to take a bath.

159
00:08:51,664 --> 00:08:52,664
Watching a shogi game again?

160
00:08:52,665 --> 00:08:54,533
It's yesterday's title match.

161
00:08:54,534 --> 00:08:55,901
All right. That's it.

162
00:08:55,902 --> 00:08:57,202
It was just getting good.

163
00:08:57,203 --> 00:08:59,771
We have a schedule,
so you can't be selfish.

164
00:08:59,772 --> 00:09:02,074
We can't change the order.

165
00:09:04,243 --> 00:09:07,479
<i>He took a bath, had his hair dried,</i>

166
00:09:07,480 --> 00:09:10,149
<i>and returned to his room
about 40 minutes later.</i>

167
00:09:12,018 --> 00:09:13,052
Oh?

168
00:09:13,853 --> 00:09:15,587
My tablet is gone.

169
00:09:15,588 --> 00:09:16,489
Huh?

170
00:09:18,190 --> 00:09:20,259
You put it away, didn't you?

171
00:09:21,294 --> 00:09:22,795
You haven't moved it, have you?

172
00:09:23,796 --> 00:09:24,830
No, I haven't.

173
00:09:27,166 --> 00:09:29,267
You'd better ask everyone first.

174
00:09:29,268 --> 00:09:30,937
We should act fast in cases like this.

175
00:09:35,241 --> 00:09:36,375
Director Etoh, look here.

176
00:09:43,549 --> 00:09:44,383
Huh?

177
00:09:45,151 --> 00:09:48,154
Why the heck is Matsu-san's tablet
in your locker?

178
00:09:49,055 --> 00:09:50,388
I have no idea.

179
00:09:50,389 --> 00:09:51,389
I really have no idea.

180
00:09:51,390 --> 00:09:53,892
What is this then?
How do you explain this?

181
00:09:53,893 --> 00:09:55,727
Betsushima, don't raise your voice.

182
00:09:55,728 --> 00:09:58,029
It wasn't me. I don't know.

183
00:09:58,030 --> 00:10:00,498
How can you not know why it's there?

184
00:10:00,499 --> 00:10:03,369
You two stay here
and don't make a scene, please.

185
00:10:04,604 --> 00:10:06,605
Yes, that's right.

186
00:10:06,606 --> 00:10:09,541
<i>I sought advice from our head office
on what to do</i>

187
00:10:09,542 --> 00:10:11,377
<i>for about five minutes, I think.</i>

188
00:10:15,481 --> 00:10:17,249
- Yes...
- Director Etoh.

189
00:10:19,352 --> 00:10:20,353
Hayakawa?

190
00:10:21,988 --> 00:10:22,822
Where's Betsushima?

191
00:10:29,462 --> 00:10:31,097
How did this happen?

192
00:10:34,233 --> 00:10:36,268
It's... nothing.

193
00:10:36,902 --> 00:10:38,738
What do you mean, nothing?

194
00:11:00,726 --> 00:11:03,562
- Excuse me. Can I open this locker?
- Yes, go ahead.

195
00:11:09,602 --> 00:11:11,570
TIEN

196
00:11:16,275 --> 00:11:20,278
Can you tell me about Mr. Betsushima,
who was with Tien?

197
00:11:20,279 --> 00:11:22,714
He is one of our more experienced
certified care workers.

198
00:11:22,715 --> 00:11:25,617
Is it possible for me to speak with him?

199
00:11:25,618 --> 00:11:28,054
Actually, he left work early yesterday
after the incident.

200
00:11:29,088 --> 00:11:32,090
And he called in sick today,
so he's not here.

201
00:11:32,091 --> 00:11:33,492
I see.

202
00:11:34,260 --> 00:11:35,628
Thank you so much.

203
00:11:36,429 --> 00:11:39,497
You're saying it's difficult
to identify the fingerprints?

204
00:11:39,498 --> 00:11:43,101
<i>There are over ten different fingerprints,
including partial ones.</i>

205
00:11:43,102 --> 00:11:46,137
I understand. Please keep me updated
on any progress.

206
00:11:46,138 --> 00:11:47,273
- <i>I will.</i>
- Thanks.

207
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:49,507
Hayakawa.

208
00:11:49,508 --> 00:11:50,476
- Take these as well.
- Okay.

209
00:11:58,417 --> 00:11:59,385
- Excuse me, sir.
- Yes?

210
00:11:59,952 --> 00:12:02,955
Sorry to bother you during your work.
I'm with the police.

211
00:12:04,323 --> 00:12:08,159
I'm investigating the theft
that occurred here yesterday.

212
00:12:08,160 --> 00:12:10,329
Do you know anything about it?

213
00:12:11,363 --> 00:12:13,331
Nothing in particular.

214
00:12:13,332 --> 00:12:14,867
Any information would be helpful.

215
00:12:19,038 --> 00:12:21,974
Tien isn't the type of person
who would steal.

216
00:12:24,710 --> 00:12:26,645
Oh, wait a minute.

217
00:12:27,213 --> 00:12:29,181
Are you the friend Tien was talking about?

218
00:12:29,982 --> 00:12:30,983
Friend?

219
00:12:32,151 --> 00:12:33,852
Is that what Tien called me?

220
00:12:33,853 --> 00:12:35,788
Yes, that's what I heard.

221
00:12:39,525 --> 00:12:40,893
I see...

222
00:12:42,261 --> 00:12:43,095
What's the matter?

223
00:12:44,964 --> 00:12:47,599
It's nothing. I'm sorry.

224
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:49,368
I have to get back to work.

225
00:12:57,576 --> 00:12:59,244
So, you're saying

226
00:12:59,245 --> 00:13:03,281
you didn't find any trace of Tien
being physically abused in the home?

227
00:13:03,282 --> 00:13:05,651
Yep. Nothing so far from my interviews.

228
00:13:07,887 --> 00:13:12,024
It's hard to say
whether he's the suspect or the victim.

229
00:13:13,993 --> 00:13:18,296
Ladies, this is Ceylon Tea, my favorite.
It's very refreshing.

230
00:13:18,297 --> 00:13:20,198
- Thank you.
- And this is for you.

231
00:13:20,199 --> 00:13:21,734
Thank you.

232
00:13:22,234 --> 00:13:24,636
When you feel like sighing,
look up and sigh.

233
00:13:24,637 --> 00:13:26,405
It turns into a good breathing exercise.

234
00:13:31,510 --> 00:13:32,878
You're right, it does.

235
00:13:35,347 --> 00:13:36,782
I sometimes wonder

236
00:13:37,416 --> 00:13:41,453
why in the world I work
as an interpreter for the police.

237
00:13:44,190 --> 00:13:45,357
Momiji?

238
00:13:47,560 --> 00:13:50,562
Many of the Vietnamese
I come across these days

239
00:13:50,563 --> 00:13:53,131
came to Japan with high aspirations.

240
00:13:53,132 --> 00:13:56,769
It doesn't matter whether
they're the suspect or the victim.

241
00:13:57,636 --> 00:14:00,371
When I interpret for them,
I hear their inner cry.

242
00:14:00,372 --> 00:14:03,742
It says, "I didn't come to Japan
to end up like this!"

243
00:14:05,244 --> 00:14:07,879
The Technical Intern Training Program

244
00:14:07,880 --> 00:14:09,981
was originally
for their home countries' development.

245
00:14:09,982 --> 00:14:13,686
Trainees are meant to use the skills
they learned here for their countries.

246
00:14:14,620 --> 00:14:16,321
Our government assumes
they will return home

247
00:14:16,322 --> 00:14:19,024
and doesn't want them to settle here.

248
00:14:19,592 --> 00:14:22,527
But companies here
have a continuous need for labor,

249
00:14:22,528 --> 00:14:23,929
creating a mismatch.

250
00:14:25,331 --> 00:14:27,232
It's the same with Japanese employees.

251
00:14:27,233 --> 00:14:30,302
Would people teach advanced technologies

252
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:33,606
to those who are expected
to leave in three to five years?

253
00:14:34,240 --> 00:14:35,174
You were listening?

254
00:14:35,841 --> 00:14:38,176
As a result, companies tend to assign

255
00:14:38,177 --> 00:14:40,546
only simple tasks
to those foreign trainees.

256
00:14:41,280 --> 00:14:43,249
That's because they go home eventually.

257
00:14:45,317 --> 00:14:46,485
I wonder

258
00:14:47,019 --> 00:14:49,388
what kind of thoughts Tien has had
while living in Japan.

259
00:14:53,893 --> 00:14:55,094
Miss Imai,

260
00:14:57,930 --> 00:14:58,797
here's a candy.

261
00:14:59,365 --> 00:15:00,398
If you like.

262
00:15:00,399 --> 00:15:01,934
Thank you.

263
00:15:02,501 --> 00:15:03,569
You're so sweet.

264
00:15:05,404 --> 00:15:07,039
See you, then.

265
00:15:17,516 --> 00:15:19,451
Fifty-three...

266
00:15:23,555 --> 00:15:27,192
Mr. Betsushima, hello?
Are you home? I'm from the police.

267
00:15:33,165 --> 00:15:35,566
I see that your lights are on.

268
00:15:35,567 --> 00:15:37,036
You're home, right?

269
00:15:39,471 --> 00:15:40,338
Gosh, so annoying!

270
00:15:40,339 --> 00:15:42,974
I'm sorry to show up like this,
but you were not at work, so...

271
00:15:42,975 --> 00:15:44,510
Whoa!

272
00:15:45,644 --> 00:15:46,879
I'm from the police.

273
00:15:50,349 --> 00:15:51,550
I see.

274
00:15:52,217 --> 00:15:54,753
- Of course, you had to call in sick.
- What do you want?

275
00:15:55,487 --> 00:15:57,990
Did Tien do that to your nose?

276
00:16:00,492 --> 00:16:01,593
No, he didn't.

277
00:16:03,662 --> 00:16:04,863
It was Hayakawa.

278
00:16:06,765 --> 00:16:07,599
What?

279
00:16:09,001 --> 00:16:10,202
What a brat he is!

280
00:16:36,729 --> 00:16:37,763
<i>Hayakawa.</i>

281
00:16:39,431 --> 00:16:41,500
Mr. Tanaka was hiding his meds again.

282
00:16:42,935 --> 00:16:45,503
I told you to make sure
that he takes them, didn't I?

283
00:16:45,504 --> 00:16:47,071
- Yes, sir.
- Don't make me repeat.

284
00:16:47,072 --> 00:16:48,073
I'm sorry.

285
00:16:49,074 --> 00:16:51,343
When will you ever become useful?

286
00:16:55,280 --> 00:16:56,548
I messed up.

287
00:16:58,817 --> 00:16:59,818
"I messed up"?

288
00:17:01,620 --> 00:17:04,990
Susumu, what does that phrase mean?

289
00:17:07,259 --> 00:17:09,595
It means that I made a mistake.

290
00:17:12,164 --> 00:17:12,998
I see.

291
00:17:13,732 --> 00:17:17,002
I MESSED UP

292
00:17:17,569 --> 00:17:18,604
<i>Thất bại.</i>

293
00:17:22,141 --> 00:17:25,477
<i>- Thất bại.
- Thất bại.</i>

294
00:17:26,078 --> 00:17:27,312
Is there an issue here?

295
00:17:29,481 --> 00:17:31,950
You're not supposed to smoke here, right?

296
00:17:33,552 --> 00:17:34,753
Leave me alone, will you?

297
00:17:35,320 --> 00:17:37,689
You should just do what you're told to do.

298
00:17:38,390 --> 00:17:40,459
You go back to your country
in three years anyway.

299
00:17:41,660 --> 00:17:44,695
We spend extra energy
in training you trainees.

300
00:17:44,696 --> 00:17:48,167
But you go home. Then we teach
another group, and they go home.

301
00:17:51,103 --> 00:17:52,838
It's totally ridiculous.

302
00:18:20,966 --> 00:18:23,569
Where is your family?

303
00:18:24,636 --> 00:18:25,471
My family?

304
00:18:26,505 --> 00:18:28,674
- You mean, my hometown?
- Yes.

305
00:18:29,141 --> 00:18:31,310
Where you were born and raised.

306
00:18:33,312 --> 00:18:36,048
It's very far.
It's a place called Okayama.

307
00:18:37,282 --> 00:18:38,617
I rarely go there, though.

308
00:18:40,385 --> 00:18:43,689
I can't go back to Vietnam, either.

309
00:18:44,723 --> 00:18:47,392
I borrowed money to come here.

310
00:18:47,893 --> 00:18:49,261
And I need to repay it first.

311
00:18:55,934 --> 00:18:56,802
But still,

312
00:18:57,936 --> 00:18:59,538
I'm lucky.

313
00:19:00,305 --> 00:19:01,240
You're lucky?

314
00:19:02,441 --> 00:19:05,543
All my friends who came to Japan with me

315
00:19:05,544 --> 00:19:07,913
are struggling with their lives here.

316
00:19:10,215 --> 00:19:11,183
But...

317
00:19:12,050 --> 00:19:13,585
People who work here

318
00:19:14,386 --> 00:19:16,121
are all very kind.

319
00:19:18,924 --> 00:19:19,858
You teach me

320
00:19:21,160 --> 00:19:23,929
kanji characters as well.

321
00:19:24,796 --> 00:19:26,098
Um, I'm...

322
00:19:27,132 --> 00:19:29,868
That's because I'm assigned to you.

323
00:19:31,236 --> 00:19:32,237
On the other hand,

324
00:19:33,172 --> 00:19:34,840
Mr. Betsushima is different.

325
00:19:35,574 --> 00:19:36,909
He is scary.

326
00:19:38,110 --> 00:19:40,245
- He's a <i>con quỷ.</i>
- <i>Con quỷ?</i>

327
00:19:41,580 --> 00:19:44,750
It means "demon" in Vietnamese.

328
00:19:45,317 --> 00:19:46,385
Demon?

329
00:19:48,820 --> 00:19:49,720
He surely is.

330
00:19:49,721 --> 00:19:51,390
<i>Con quỷ!</i>

331
00:19:57,396 --> 00:19:58,430
Tien...

332
00:20:13,212 --> 00:20:15,079
Look. Here's trouble.

333
00:20:15,080 --> 00:20:18,116
Hey, it's great to see you.
Were you waiting for me?

334
00:20:22,654 --> 00:20:24,690
I guess you were not.

335
00:20:26,058 --> 00:20:27,025
I'll have the usual.

336
00:20:27,526 --> 00:20:28,360
Sure.

337
00:20:38,237 --> 00:20:39,504
You don't like me?

338
00:20:40,439 --> 00:20:41,506
I didn't say that.

339
00:20:43,408 --> 00:20:47,045
It's not right to judge something
before actually tasting it.

340
00:20:48,981 --> 00:20:50,015
What do you mean by that?

341
00:20:53,051 --> 00:20:54,386
With booze,

342
00:20:54,987 --> 00:20:57,356
can you tell the taste
just by looking at the label?

343
00:20:58,824 --> 00:21:01,827
You can't tell unless you roll it
on your tongue, can you?

344
00:21:06,531 --> 00:21:09,268
It's not good to judge something
only by its appearance.

345
00:21:09,768 --> 00:21:11,603
The Japanese are infamous for that.

346
00:21:13,772 --> 00:21:15,741
You're Japanese too, aren't you?

347
00:21:17,175 --> 00:21:18,776
You'll have the pleasure

348
00:21:18,777 --> 00:21:21,747
of finding that out
only after tasting it, don't you think?

349
00:21:24,616 --> 00:21:26,952
I'm sorry,
but I'm staying away from booze.

350
00:21:33,025 --> 00:21:34,693
I do feel sorry for you.

351
00:21:35,827 --> 00:21:36,662
Give me another one.

352
00:22:05,190 --> 00:22:08,894
You're off-limits. You're involved
with Mr. Osada's daughter, right?

353
00:22:09,461 --> 00:22:12,296
That match was imposed by him.

354
00:22:12,297 --> 00:22:14,566
Oda, we're still on for Friday, right?

355
00:22:15,300 --> 00:22:17,435
Actually, my sister is visiting me
that day.

356
00:22:17,436 --> 00:22:19,171
I know you're totally lying right now.

357
00:22:28,213 --> 00:22:29,181
Hello.

358
00:22:30,782 --> 00:22:31,683
Tien.

359
00:22:32,184 --> 00:22:34,552
- Tien!
- Mr. Matsumura.

360
00:22:34,553 --> 00:22:37,556
- Tien is not here today.
- What?

361
00:22:38,056 --> 00:22:39,925
- Hello there.
- Oh, hi.

362
00:22:40,559 --> 00:22:42,694
Sir, are you looking for Tien?

363
00:22:43,328 --> 00:22:44,795
It has to be Tien.

364
00:22:44,796 --> 00:22:48,266
Only he understands how to scrub my back.

365
00:22:49,634 --> 00:22:51,203
He must be very good at it.

366
00:22:51,703 --> 00:22:52,671
Are you serious?

367
00:22:53,472 --> 00:22:57,608
All along, I thought
you were angry with Tien.

368
00:22:57,609 --> 00:23:00,378
I'm angry at Hayakawa, though,

369
00:23:00,379 --> 00:23:02,680
because it hurts when he washes my back.

370
00:23:02,681 --> 00:23:03,849
I prefer Tien.

371
00:23:04,416 --> 00:23:05,917
I'm glad I know it now.

372
00:23:06,518 --> 00:23:07,386
Goodbye.

373
00:23:12,057 --> 00:23:13,191
Yoo-hoo!

374
00:23:14,760 --> 00:23:16,727
Oh, hello.

375
00:23:16,728 --> 00:23:17,929
Can you give me a moment?

376
00:23:19,965 --> 00:23:20,799
Okay.

377
00:23:22,300 --> 00:23:24,669
It's chilly, isn't it?

378
00:23:25,737 --> 00:23:27,071
I brought something.

379
00:23:27,072 --> 00:23:29,641
This is a Vietnamese dessert called <i>Chè.</i>

380
00:23:30,642 --> 00:23:32,744
I thought you might be a little hungry.

381
00:23:33,445 --> 00:23:35,713
No, thank you. I can't take it from you.

382
00:23:35,714 --> 00:23:39,117
It's all right. I'm eating it, too. Here.

383
00:23:42,587 --> 00:23:45,055
It's made with a perfect combination

384
00:23:45,056 --> 00:23:47,359
of banana, tapioca, and coconut milk.

385
00:23:48,927 --> 00:23:49,928
Thank you.

386
00:23:50,495 --> 00:23:51,863
Let's devour it.

387
00:23:56,301 --> 00:23:57,569
Thanks.

388
00:24:07,345 --> 00:24:10,148
- How is it? What do you think?
- It's very nice.

389
00:24:10,949 --> 00:24:12,484
It is, isn't it?

390
00:24:20,992 --> 00:24:22,928
I heard about what happened

391
00:24:23,462 --> 00:24:25,363
the day before yesterday
from Mr. Betsushima.

392
00:24:28,099 --> 00:24:29,234
Huh?

393
00:24:38,777 --> 00:24:41,213
Why the heck is Matsu-san's tablet
in your locker?

394
00:24:41,847 --> 00:24:44,114
It wasn't me. I don't know.

395
00:24:44,115 --> 00:24:45,583
How can you not know why it's there?

396
00:24:45,584 --> 00:24:48,653
You two stay here
and don't make a scene, please.

397
00:24:51,990 --> 00:24:54,793
Why? I'm not the one who stole it.

398
00:24:55,360 --> 00:24:56,695
- You must know that well.
- Shut up!

399
00:24:58,497 --> 00:25:01,099
It doesn't matter
whether you're a thief or not.

400
00:25:02,334 --> 00:25:05,669
People may like and flatter you,

401
00:25:05,670 --> 00:25:10,208
but if they hear that you've stolen,
they will all say, "Of course!"

402
00:25:11,576 --> 00:25:14,246
You told the director
about my smoking, didn't you?

403
00:25:14,913 --> 00:25:18,082
I also heard that you submitted
a leave request.

404
00:25:18,083 --> 00:25:19,917
What's the Lunar New Year anyway?

405
00:25:19,918 --> 00:25:22,486
There's no such custom in Japan.

406
00:25:22,487 --> 00:25:24,788
Wait. Please stop. He didn't do it.

407
00:25:24,789 --> 00:25:26,524
Stay out of it.

408
00:25:26,525 --> 00:25:27,893
Are you even aware

409
00:25:28,560 --> 00:25:30,694
that these guys will steal your jobs?

410
00:25:30,695 --> 00:25:34,566
Useless and incapable people like you
will lose your job because of these guys.

411
00:25:38,336 --> 00:25:40,672
Now listen. You know what I'm doing?

412
00:25:41,239 --> 00:25:43,073
You're just a loser,

413
00:25:43,074 --> 00:25:45,543
having fun being buddy-buddy
in your daydream.

414
00:25:45,544 --> 00:25:49,347
So, I'm teaching you how tough reality is.
You'd better be grateful.

415
00:25:57,489 --> 00:25:58,723
Don’t look down on my friend.

416
00:26:00,392 --> 00:26:02,960
He helped me with everything,
from Japanese to work.

417
00:26:02,961 --> 00:26:04,361
In what way is he useless?

418
00:26:04,362 --> 00:26:06,064
What do you even know, aside from yelling?

419
00:26:06,631 --> 00:26:09,601
- Shut up! Speak Japanese.
- Stop.

420
00:26:11,570 --> 00:26:13,471
Ouch.

421
00:26:16,508 --> 00:26:17,475
You little...

422
00:26:23,448 --> 00:26:26,251
Come on, you two.
Quit your jobs here together.

423
00:26:35,727 --> 00:26:38,797
Mr. Betsushima,
who was assisting with bathing,

424
00:26:39,631 --> 00:26:42,067
knew very well
that Tien couldn't have stolen it.

425
00:26:49,708 --> 00:26:51,142
It was you, wasn't it?

426
00:26:54,145 --> 00:26:56,247
Did you put the tablet in his locker?

427
00:27:02,921 --> 00:27:03,755
But...

428
00:27:05,590 --> 00:27:07,926
there must have been some reason.

429
00:27:21,306 --> 00:27:22,974
When I first met him...

430
00:27:24,943 --> 00:27:26,077
When I met Tien,

431
00:27:27,312 --> 00:27:29,848
he said that I was the same as him.

432
00:27:35,253 --> 00:27:37,255
Susumu Hayakawa.

433
00:27:39,057 --> 00:27:42,093
Susumu is the same with Tien.

434
00:27:45,263 --> 00:27:46,197
Same as you?

435
00:27:50,735 --> 00:27:52,937
<i>At first I didn't understand
what he meant.</i>

436
00:27:54,639 --> 00:27:56,941
But in a way we did look alike, I thought.

437
00:27:58,777 --> 00:28:00,211
We're around the same age,

438
00:28:01,146 --> 00:28:02,914
and we're both underlings.

439
00:28:12,290 --> 00:28:13,391
Susumu,

440
00:28:14,426 --> 00:28:16,927
aren't you off today?

441
00:28:16,928 --> 00:28:21,832
It's January 1st.
It's Japanese New Year, isn't it?

442
00:28:21,833 --> 00:28:26,704
You're right, but it's all right.
I don't go visit my folks,

443
00:28:26,705 --> 00:28:28,306
and I'm alone at home anyway.

444
00:28:29,074 --> 00:28:30,442
You're working today, too.

445
00:28:32,444 --> 00:28:35,280
It's kind of sad, though.

446
00:28:36,514 --> 00:28:38,850
I'll go get changed.

447
00:28:45,256 --> 00:28:48,159
<i>He is away from home, just like me.</i>

448
00:28:49,861 --> 00:28:51,429
<i>He's away from his family</i>

449
00:28:53,832 --> 00:28:55,333
<i>and has no friends here.</i>

450
00:28:58,136 --> 00:28:59,404
<i>He's totally alone.</i>

451
00:29:02,507 --> 00:29:05,944
<i>And every day,
we both get yelled at by Mr. Betsushima.</i>

452
00:29:09,647 --> 00:29:12,484
<i>Maybe that's why I thought</i>

453
00:29:13,451 --> 00:29:15,286
<i>we could be friends.</i>

454
00:29:17,322 --> 00:29:18,423
<i>Because he looked...</i>

455
00:29:19,991 --> 00:29:22,327
more miserable than I did.

456
00:29:27,832 --> 00:29:30,802
But one day, I realized something.

457
00:29:34,172 --> 00:29:36,407
I realized that maybe I was the one

458
00:29:38,777 --> 00:29:40,712
who looked more miserable.

459
00:29:41,513 --> 00:29:46,651
Hello everyone, quite a crowd here!
Hello, guys!

460
00:29:47,218 --> 00:29:49,954
I'm working right now,
but I'll be done soon.

461
00:30:12,443 --> 00:30:14,479
Would you like to come along?

462
00:30:15,480 --> 00:30:17,215
- <i>Tet?</i>
- Yes.

463
00:30:17,782 --> 00:30:19,884
It's the Vietnamese Lunar New Year.

464
00:30:20,785 --> 00:30:24,889
I'm sure
you'll have a wonderful time, too.

465
00:30:29,794 --> 00:30:33,197
This is a picture of my family
and relatives

466
00:30:33,198 --> 00:30:35,867
from when we got together.

467
00:30:37,235 --> 00:30:40,638
This is my father

468
00:30:41,606 --> 00:30:42,473
and my mother.

469
00:30:43,775 --> 00:30:47,445
And this is my brother's child and...

470
00:30:50,748 --> 00:30:53,183
When Hayakawa does it, it's painful

471
00:30:53,184 --> 00:30:56,387
because he scratches my back too hard.

472
00:30:56,888 --> 00:30:58,723
Oh no! That's horrible.

473
00:31:00,959 --> 00:31:03,694
You do it so much better.

474
00:31:03,695 --> 00:31:05,129
That's not true.

475
00:31:50,875 --> 00:31:52,010
<i>Mr. Hayakawa,</i>

476
00:31:53,411 --> 00:31:57,348
did you want to see Tien gone
from your workplace?

477
00:32:01,586 --> 00:32:05,156
If a charge is filed against him,
he may have to quit this job.

478
00:32:05,857 --> 00:32:08,226
Then, he'll have to return
to his home country.

479
00:32:10,828 --> 00:32:13,031
If he has somewhere to return,
he can just go.

480
00:32:15,800 --> 00:32:18,369
He has family and friends who love him,

481
00:32:19,737 --> 00:32:22,106
and he even has a wife waiting for him.

482
00:32:24,475 --> 00:32:28,446
People have high expectations of him,
and he has the ability to meet them.

483
00:32:30,782 --> 00:32:32,716
If he continues working in Japan,

484
00:32:32,717 --> 00:32:34,819
he will be one
of the successful Vietnamese.

485
00:32:36,421 --> 00:32:38,156
On the other hand, I...

486
00:32:41,025 --> 00:32:42,493
I have nothing.

487
00:32:46,931 --> 00:32:49,600
While you can accept someone below you,

488
00:32:50,501 --> 00:32:52,070
do you repel him when he's a threat?

489
00:32:57,475 --> 00:32:58,843
Tien was...

490
00:32:59,677 --> 00:33:01,312
Though he was in so much pain,

491
00:33:02,480 --> 00:33:04,749
he tried to hide the fracture in his hand.

492
00:33:07,118 --> 00:33:08,152
Do you know why?

493
00:33:13,124 --> 00:33:14,726
He was trying to protect you.

494
00:33:21,299 --> 00:33:26,236
He didn't want the police to find out
that you hurt Mr. Betsushima,

495
00:33:26,237 --> 00:33:27,872
so he kept silent about it.

496
00:33:30,608 --> 00:33:33,277
I think the reason Susumu helped me

497
00:33:36,180 --> 00:33:38,316
was because I appeared
to be a helpless, miserable foreigner.

498
00:33:44,722 --> 00:33:46,891
<i>But when it's based on mere sympathy,</i>

499
00:33:49,360 --> 00:33:51,329
<i>can you say it is true friendship?</i>

500
00:33:56,501 --> 00:34:00,838
<i>It was always Susumu who helped me,
not the other way around,</i>

501
00:34:03,174 --> 00:34:05,309
<i>but someday,
I want to be able to offer help to him.</i>

502
00:34:08,813 --> 00:34:10,648
Don't you dare insult my friend!

503
00:34:11,716 --> 00:34:15,819
Do you know how much he's helped me
with the language and the job here?

504
00:34:15,820 --> 00:34:17,955
How dare you call him useless!

505
00:34:19,757 --> 00:34:22,160
We needed each other.

506
00:34:23,494 --> 00:34:25,763
<i>I wanted him to see me</i>

507
00:34:27,665 --> 00:34:30,535
<i>as someone he needed.</i>

508
00:34:34,605 --> 00:34:38,943
Not just being allowed to be by his side
because he pities me.

509
00:34:43,381 --> 00:34:46,150
You said you don't have anything,

510
00:34:47,652 --> 00:34:49,320
but is it really true?

511
00:34:53,157 --> 00:34:54,459
You do have something.

512
00:34:55,460 --> 00:34:57,562
I think you do have a faithful friend

513
00:34:58,496 --> 00:35:00,898
who wants to protect you.

514
00:35:10,441 --> 00:35:12,410
Now about this incident.

515
00:35:13,911 --> 00:35:15,746
Neither Mr. Matsumura, Mr. Betsushima,

516
00:35:16,914 --> 00:35:22,086
nor Tien has voiced any intent
to claim damages against you.

517
00:35:23,387 --> 00:35:24,255
Therefore,

518
00:35:25,189 --> 00:35:27,892
the police will not pursue this case.

519
00:35:36,167 --> 00:35:37,001
Um...

520
00:35:42,039 --> 00:35:43,040
Do you think

521
00:35:45,143 --> 00:35:47,078
Tien will ever forgive me?

522
00:36:01,159 --> 00:36:05,062
With more foreigners, it gets less safe
and the crime rate goes up.

523
00:36:05,963 --> 00:36:08,065
Look at Europe
with its migration policies.

524
00:36:09,433 --> 00:36:13,804
Even so, Japan wants to keep
bringing in more foreigners.

525
00:36:14,539 --> 00:36:16,007
What will happen then?

526
00:36:16,641 --> 00:36:19,142
When minorities are not minorities
anymore,

527
00:36:19,143 --> 00:36:22,513
they will start making noise,
demanding more rights.

528
00:36:23,614 --> 00:36:27,852
They even forget that we're doing them
a favor by allowing them to work here.

529
00:36:30,988 --> 00:36:31,822
Are you done?

530
00:36:32,857 --> 00:36:35,625
Tayama, send this guy home.

531
00:36:35,626 --> 00:36:36,527
Yes, sir.

532
00:36:39,363 --> 00:36:40,331
You can go now.

533
00:36:46,037 --> 00:36:47,405
Can I say something?

534
00:36:51,275 --> 00:36:52,810
This is for your future's sake.

535
00:36:53,377 --> 00:36:54,378
What do you want?

536
00:36:56,080 --> 00:36:59,015
It's not that we're "allowing" them
to work here.

537
00:36:59,016 --> 00:37:02,720
They are the ones doing us a favor
by working in this country.

538
00:37:03,554 --> 00:37:04,621
What are you talking about?

539
00:37:04,622 --> 00:37:08,225
Our population has decreased,
resulting in fewer children.

540
00:37:08,226 --> 00:37:12,029
Our labor and consumption levels
are insufficient to sustain society.

541
00:37:13,097 --> 00:37:14,465
Japan cannot be sustained

542
00:37:14,999 --> 00:37:16,567
by the Japanese alone anymore.

543
00:37:19,303 --> 00:37:21,305
I won't tell you
that you have to love foreigners.

544
00:37:22,306 --> 00:37:26,843
But... No matter how much you antagonize
and exclude them,

545
00:37:26,844 --> 00:37:28,980
you can't maintain your place in society.

546
00:37:31,449 --> 00:37:33,651
As someone who shares
a community with them,

547
00:37:34,318 --> 00:37:35,653
you must at least accept them.

548
00:37:38,956 --> 00:37:40,958
Or you will end up in agony yourself.

549
00:37:45,029 --> 00:37:48,332
Japan is changing already.

550
00:38:14,325 --> 00:38:15,326
Tien.

551
00:38:32,877 --> 00:38:33,978
"I messed up."

552
00:38:47,024 --> 00:38:48,359
Mr. Hayakawa,

553
00:38:49,393 --> 00:38:50,428
don't look away.

554
00:39:00,838 --> 00:39:02,573
Don't make the same mistake.

555
00:39:04,008 --> 00:39:05,009
Understand

556
00:39:05,943 --> 00:39:08,346
who he is to you.

557
00:39:23,794 --> 00:39:25,795
Everyone, this is my colleague.

558
00:39:25,796 --> 00:39:28,732
- Hello!
- Hello!

559
00:39:28,733 --> 00:39:29,967
Oh!

560
00:39:30,768 --> 00:39:32,335
Yikes!

561
00:39:32,336 --> 00:39:34,170
What do you mean "yikes"?

562
00:39:34,171 --> 00:39:36,507
Arikino has been pretty nice lately.

563
00:39:37,074 --> 00:39:39,876
Wow, they look delicious, too.

564
00:39:39,877 --> 00:39:42,445
These are traditional dishes
for the Vietnamese New Year.

565
00:39:42,446 --> 00:39:44,547
Though it's a little early.

566
00:39:44,548 --> 00:39:46,783
Momiji made all of this.

567
00:39:46,784 --> 00:39:48,284
- Don't you think it's amazing?
- Amazing!

568
00:39:48,285 --> 00:39:50,420
I used to work at a Vietnamese restaurant.

569
00:39:50,421 --> 00:39:52,288
And that's where I met my friend, Akira.

570
00:39:52,289 --> 00:39:54,190
Hi, there. I'm Akira.

571
00:39:54,191 --> 00:39:57,427
- Akira is a Vietnamese, born in Japan.
- Yes.

572
00:39:57,428 --> 00:39:59,095
Is this your first time to try it?

573
00:39:59,096 --> 00:40:01,699
- Yes, it is. It looks so good.
- Please try it.

574
00:40:04,301 --> 00:40:05,536
How is it?

575
00:40:06,203 --> 00:40:09,039
- It's delicious.
- I'm so happy.

576
00:40:11,909 --> 00:40:13,810
- How is it?
- What do you think?

577
00:40:13,811 --> 00:40:15,112
This is really good!

578
00:40:15,846 --> 00:40:16,814
It's tasty!

579
00:40:19,450 --> 00:40:21,184
Five and two.

580
00:40:21,185 --> 00:40:25,188
The interns who come to Japan
are full of aspirations and ambitions,

581
00:40:25,189 --> 00:40:28,558
determined to seize opportunities
at all costs, right?

582
00:40:28,559 --> 00:40:31,462
That's why our society must become a place

583
00:40:32,096 --> 00:40:34,965
where foreigners can live
with more choices available.

584
00:40:36,367 --> 00:40:38,702
There have to be more people like you.

585
00:40:39,236 --> 00:40:41,938
Then, the relationship between
the Japanese and Vietnamese expats

586
00:40:41,939 --> 00:40:43,707
would improve, I'm sure.

587
00:40:44,308 --> 00:40:45,709
- Huh?
- I mean...

588
00:40:47,044 --> 00:40:51,315
I think it's very significant
that you're working as an interpreter.

589
00:40:52,416 --> 00:40:53,851
Mr. Arikino...

590
00:40:54,985 --> 00:40:58,823
Oh my goodness!
Arikeeno is giving a compliment.

591
00:41:01,725 --> 00:41:05,029
Minh, can I have that wine over there?

592
00:41:05,830 --> 00:41:08,231
- Of course.
- Thank you.

593
00:41:08,232 --> 00:41:10,200
- Here you go.
- Thank you so much.

594
00:41:10,201 --> 00:41:11,302
No problem.

595
00:41:11,936 --> 00:41:14,170
Did he just call you Minh?

596
00:41:14,171 --> 00:41:18,074
Ah, yes.
That's because my real name is Minh.

597
00:41:18,075 --> 00:41:19,242
- What?
- Yeah.

598
00:41:19,243 --> 00:41:21,678
Vietnam is also part
of the Chinese Character Cultural Sphere,

599
00:41:21,679 --> 00:41:23,681
so we use kanji characters for names.

600
00:41:25,516 --> 00:41:27,584
The Chinese character

601
00:41:27,585 --> 00:41:29,920
for "Minh" is the one you use
for the word "bright" in Japanese.

602
00:41:32,790 --> 00:41:36,093
That's why my friends call me "Akira"
in Japanese.

603
00:41:36,727 --> 00:41:38,529
I see.

604
00:41:39,497 --> 00:41:43,566
Is there a Chinese character
for the name "Tien"?

605
00:41:43,567 --> 00:41:44,835
For "Tien"?

606
00:41:51,275 --> 00:41:52,343
The one that reads "Susumu" in Japanese.

607
00:42:00,050 --> 00:42:01,985
Interesting...

608
00:42:01,986 --> 00:42:05,523
Susumu is the same with Tien.

609
00:42:08,459 --> 00:42:09,460
Same as you?

610
00:42:36,020 --> 00:42:36,854
Miss Koda?

611
00:42:38,956 --> 00:42:41,492
Whoa, you totally scared me!

612
00:42:42,192 --> 00:42:45,062
Why didn't you tell me you were here?

613
00:42:47,364 --> 00:42:48,766
What's the matter?

614
00:42:55,973 --> 00:42:57,274
Tell me, Arikeeno?

615
00:42:59,510 --> 00:43:01,779
Do you think friendship can be restored

616
00:43:03,013 --> 00:43:04,315
even after it's broken?

617
00:43:08,018 --> 00:43:10,554
Are you talking about Susumu and Tien?

618
00:43:21,665 --> 00:43:25,069
Well, since both of them are still young,

619
00:43:27,071 --> 00:43:29,406
I bet they have a chance
to become friends again.

620
00:43:32,543 --> 00:43:33,911
At least,

621
00:43:34,645 --> 00:43:38,549
they're still living in the same country
at this point.

622
00:43:49,793 --> 00:43:51,462
In the same country...

623
00:44:06,310 --> 00:44:08,746
And maybe
you brought your boyfriend along?

624
00:44:09,580 --> 00:44:10,446
<i>Yakusoku...</i>

625
00:44:10,447 --> 00:44:13,016
<i>Being able to connect with anyone</i>

626
00:44:13,017 --> 00:44:14,351
is a gift you have, Mari.

627
00:44:15,552 --> 00:44:16,786
<i>Why were you crying?</i>

628
00:44:16,787 --> 00:44:19,155
<i>You mean, Lieutenant Agawa? But he is...</i>

629
00:44:19,156 --> 00:44:22,892
<i>You are more important to me
than anyone else.</i>

630
00:44:22,893 --> 00:44:26,263
<i>That's why I decided I wanted to become
a police officer that day.</i>
